le_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"inconsistent_home_away_resolution"},{"dimension":"logic_clarity","identifier":"season_fetch_status_conflates_missing_and_failed","summary":"Season fetch flow collapses transient failures into the same \"missing\" branch","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["fetch_game_json_with_retry() lines 93-103 retries 403/404, retryable HTTP codes, and request exceptions, but after all retries it always returns `(\\\"missing\\\", None)` rather than distinguishing a confirmed missing game from a failed fetch.","process_game() lines 153-155 then maps every non-`ok` result to `{\"status\": \"missing\"}`, so downstream counts can report network/server failures as missing games instead of failed games."],"suggestion":"Return distinct terminal statuses such as `missing` and `failed`, preserve them in `process_game()`, and let `compute_season()` count each case separately so the summary matches what actually happened.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"single_edit","root_cause_cluster":"status_path_collapse"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Outcome branches are sometimes written as convenience fallbacks instead of explicit state handling.","Similar logic is reimplemented in multiple scripts, so one safer branch structure did not propagate to neighboring code."],"likely_symptoms":["score_side_fallback_defaults_to_away","season_fetch_status_conflates_missing_and_failed"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
